&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 9.7%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=9% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;440
130&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.5%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=2% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 1.3%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 9.7%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=9% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#8212;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.5%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=2% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 1.3%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 9.7%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=9% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;384
778&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Considerable judgment is required in interpreting market data to develop the estimate of fair value of our derivative instruments.&amp;#160; Accordingly
 the estimate may not be indicative of the amounts that we could realize in a current market exchange.&amp;#160; The use of different market assumptions or valuation methodologies could have a material effect on the estimated fair value amounts.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Derivative Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We utilize interest rate swaps in the management of our variable interest rate exposure and do not enter into derivatives for trading purposes.&amp;#160; All derivatives are measured at fair value.&amp;#160; Our interest rate swaps are classified as cash flow hedges.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Cash and Cash Equivalents&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We consider all highly liquid investments purchased with an original maturity of three months or less to be cash equivalents.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Accounts Receivable&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Accounts receivable consist primarily of receivables from customers and distributors for products purchased.&amp;#160; Receivables are past due when they are unpaid greater than thirty days.&amp;#160; We determine any required reserves by considering a number of factors
 including the length of time the accounts receivable have been outstanding
 and our loss history.&amp;#160; We maintain an allowance for doubtful accounts for estimated losses resulting from the inability of our customers to make required payments.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Inventories&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Inventories are stated at the lower of cost (first-in
 first-out) or market.&amp;#160; We identify slow moving or obsolete inventories and estimate appropriate write-down provisions related thereto.&amp;#160; If actual market conditions are less favorable than those projected by management
 additional inventory write-downs may be required.&amp;#160; In the ordinary course of business
 we manage price and supply risk of commodities by entering into various short-term purchase arrangements with our vendors.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Property and Equipment&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Property and equipment are recorded at cost.&amp;#160; Cost includes expenditures for major improvements and replacements.&amp;#160; Maintenance and repairs are charged to operations when incurred.&amp;#160; When assets are retired or otherwise disposed of
 the related costs and accumulated depreciation are removed from the appropriate accounts
 and the resulting gain or loss is recognized. &amp;#160;Depreciation expense is computed using the straight-line method over the estimated useful lives of the assets
 ranging from two to thirty years.&amp;#160; We capitalize certain computer software and software development costs incurred in connection with developing or obtaining computer software for internal use.&amp;#160; Capitalized software costs are included in property
 plant and equipment and amortized on a straight-line basis when placed into service over three years.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We evaluate the recoverability of property and equipment not held for sale by comparing the carrying amount of the asset or group of assets against the estimated undiscounted future cash flows expected to result from the use of the asset or group of assets and their eventual disposition
 in accordance with relevant authoritative guidance.&amp;#160; If the undiscounted future cash flows are less than the carrying value of the asset or group of assets being evaluated
 an impairment loss is recorded.&amp;#160; The loss is measured as the difference between the fair value and carrying value of the asset or group of assets being evaluated.&amp;#160; Assets to be disposed of are reported at the lower of the carrying amount or the fair value less cost to sell.&amp;#160; The estimated fair value would be based on the best information available under the circumstances
 including prices for similar assets or the results of valuation techniques
 including the present value of expected future cash flows using a discount rate commensurate with the risks involved.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Goodwill and trademarks are reviewed for impairment annually or more frequently if impairment indicators arise.&amp;#160; Goodwill
 by reporting unit
 is required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change that more-likely-than-not reduces the fair value of a reporting unit below its carrying value.&amp;#160; We have concluded from our annual impairment testing performed in December&amp;#160;that neither of our two reporting units were at risk of failing the impairment test in the near term
 and we believe that there are no known risks for that conclusion to change at either of our reporting units.&amp;#160; Intangible assets with indefinite lives are required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change indicating that the asset might be impaired.&amp;#160; Amortizable intangible assets are amortized using the straight-line method over their estimated useful lives
 which is the estimated period over which economic benefits are expected to be provided.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Management believes that each of our trademarks has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely
 and therefore each of our trademarks has been determined to have an indefinite life.&amp;#160; Management&amp;#8217;s determination that our trademarks have indefinite lives includes an evaluation of historical cash flows and projected cash flows for each of these trademarks.&amp;#160; In addition
 there are no legal
 regulatory
 contractual
 economic or other factors to limit the useful life of these trademarks
 and management intends to renew each of these trademarks
 which can be accomplished at little cost.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;See Note 2 &amp;#8220;Goodwill
 Trademarks
 and Other Intangible Assets&amp;#8221; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Self-Insurance Reserves&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We are partially self-insured for the purposes of providing health care benefits to employees covered by our insurance plan.&amp;#160; The plan covers all full-time employees of the Company on the first day of the month after hiring date for salaried employees
 and the first day of the month following the ninetieth day of service for hourly employees.&amp;#160; The plan covers the employee&amp;#8217;s dependents
 if elected by the employee.&amp;#160; We have contracted with an insurance carrier for stop loss coverage that commences when $75
000 in claims is paid annually for a covered participant.&amp;#160; In addition
 we have contracted for aggregate stop loss insurance which provides coverage after the maximum amount paid by us exceeds approximately $1.5 million.&amp;#160; Estimated unpaid claims included in accrued liabilities amount to $0.4 million and $0.3 million at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 respectively.&amp;#160; These amounts represent management&amp;#8217;s best estimate of amounts that have not been paid prior to the year-end dates.&amp;#160; It is reasonably possible that the expense we will ultimately incur could differ.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;In accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States
 we recognize operating revenues upon shipment of products to customers provided title and risk of loss pass to our customers.&amp;#160; In those instances where title and risk of loss does not pass until delivery
 revenue recognition is deferred until delivery has occurred.&amp;#160; In our snack products segment
 revenue for products sold through our local distribution network prior to the sale of this business in November&amp;#160;2012
 was recognized when the product is received by the retailer.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Provisions and allowances for sales returns
 promotional allowances
 coupon redemption and discounts are also recorded as a reduction of revenues in our consolidated financial statements.&amp;#160; These allowances are estimated based on a percentage of sales returns using historical and current market information.&amp;#160; We record certain reductions to revenue for promotional allowances.&amp;#160; There are several different types of promotional allowances such as off-invoice allowances
 rebates and shelf space allowances.&amp;#160; An off-invoice allowance is a reduction of the sales price that is directly deducted from the invoice amount.&amp;#160; We record the amount of the deduction as a reduction to revenue when the transaction occurs.&amp;#160; We record certain allowances for coupon redemptions
 scan-back promotions and other promotional activities as a reduction to revenue.&amp;#160; Anytime we offer consideration (cash or credit) as a trade advertising or promotional allowance to a purchaser of products at any point along the distribution chain
 the amount is accrued and recorded as a reduction in revenue.&amp;#160; Costs associated with obtaining shelf space (i.e.
 &amp;#8220;slotting fees&amp;#8221;) are accounted for as a reduction of revenue in the period in which we incur such costs.&amp;#160; The accrued liabilities for these allowances are monitored throughout the time period covered by the coupon or promotion.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Marketing Costs&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We recorded $0.9 million and $1.0 million
 in fiscal years 2012 and 2011 respectively
 for advertising costs which are included in selling
 general and administrative expenses on the Consolidated Statements of Operations.&amp;#160; These costs include various sponsorships
 coupon administration and consumer advertising programs that we enter into throughout the year
 and are expensed as incurred.&amp;#160; We are a national co-sponsor of American Rivers
 a leading conservation organization protecting and restoring America&amp;#8217;s rivers.&amp;#160; We are allowed to use the American Rivers mark on packaging and printed materials as well as directly promote products to members and river cleanup volunteers.&amp;#160; Our marketing programs also include selective event sponsorship designed to increase brand awareness and to provide opportunities to mass sample branded products.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Also included in selling
 general and administrative expense are costs and fees relating to the execution of in-store product demonstrations with club stores or grocery retailers
 which were $1.9 million and $3.6 million for the years ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively.&amp;#160; The cost of product used in the demonstrations
 which is insignificant
 and the fee we pay to the independent third party providers who conduct the in-store demonstrations
 are recorded as expense when the event occurs.&amp;#160; Product demonstrations are conducted by independent third party providers designated by the various retailer or club chains.&amp;#160; During the in-store demonstrations
 the consumers in the stores receive small samples of our products
 and consumers are not required to purchase our product in order to receive the sample.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Shipping and Handling&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Shipping and handling costs are included in cost of revenues.&amp;#160; We do not bill customers for freight.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We account for income taxes under the asset and liability method
 which requires the recognition of deferred tax assets and liabilities for the expected future tax consequences of events that have been included in the financial statements.&amp;#160; Under this method
 deferred tax assets and liabilities are determined based on the differences between the financial statements and tax basis of assets and liabilities using enacted tax rates in effect for the year in which the differences are expected to reverse.&amp;#160; The effect of a change in tax rates on deferred tax assets and liabilities is recognized in income in the period that includes the enactment date.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We record net deferred tax assets to the extent we believe these assets will more likely than not be realized.&amp;#160; In making such determination
 we consider all available positive and negative evidence
 including future reversals of existing taxable temporary differences
 projected future taxable income
 tax planning strategies and recent financial operations.&amp;#160; Failure to achieve forecasted taxable income in applicable tax jurisdictions could affect the ultimate realization of deferred tax assets and could result in an increase in our effective tax rate on future earnings.&amp;#160; A valuation allowance is provided when it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized.&amp;#160; The authoritative guidance provides that a tax benefit from an uncertain tax position may be recognized when it is more likely than not that the position will be sustained upon examination
 including resolutions of any related appeals or litigation processes
 based on the technical merits.&amp;#160; The tax benefit is measured based on the largest benefit that has a greater than 50% likelihood of being realized upon ultimate settlement&lt;i&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;It is our policy to recognize interest and penalties accrued on any unrecognized tax benefits as a component of income tax expense.&amp;#160; We do not have any accrued interest or penalties associated with any unrecognized tax benefits
 nor was any interest or penalties recorded during the years ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We file income tax returns in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and various state jurisdictions.&amp;#160; Our U.S. federal income tax returns for years 2009 through 2011 remain open to examination by the Internal Revenue Service.&amp;#160; Our state tax returns for years 2008 through 2011 remain open to examination by the state jurisdictions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Stock Options and Stock-Based Compensation&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Stock options and other stock based compensation awards expense are adjusted for estimated forfeitures and are recognized on a straight-line basis over the requisite period of the award
 which is currently one to five years for stock options
 and one to three years for restricted stock.&amp;#160; We estimate future forfeiture rates based on our historical experience.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Compensation costs related to all stock-based payment arrangements
 including employee stock options
 are recognized in the financial statements based on the fair value method of accounting.&amp;#160; Excess tax benefits related to stock-based payment arrangements are classified as cash inflows from financing activities and cash outflows from operating activities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;See Note 8 &amp;#8220;Shareholders&amp;#8217; Equity&amp;#8221; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Earnings Per Common Share&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Basic earnings per common share is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of shares of common stock outstanding during the period.&amp;#160; Diluted earnings per share is calculated by including all dilutive common shares such as stock options and restricted stock.&amp;#160; For the year ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 options to purchase 281
017 shares of our Common Stock were excluded from the calculation of diluted earnings per share because their effects were antidilutive.&amp;#160; For the year ended December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 options to purchase 215
500 shares of our Common Stock were excluded from the calculation of diluted earnings per share because their effects were antidilutive.&amp;#160; These exclusions were made because the options&amp;#8217; exercise prices were greater than the average market price of our common stock for those periods.&amp;#160; Exercises of outstanding stock options or warrants are assumed to occur for purposes of calculating diluted earnings per share for periods in which their effect would not be anti-dilutive.&amp;#160; Earnings per common share was computed as follows for the years ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table style=MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in; WIDTH: 93.34%; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=93% border=0&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=1&gt;December&amp;#160;29

2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 12.82%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 1pt solid valign=bottom width=12% colspan=2&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=1&gt;December&amp;#160;31
&lt;br /&gt;
2011&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.04%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -10pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Basic Earnings Per Share:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.68%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=2% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 12.82%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none valign=bottom width=12% bgcolor=#CCEEFF colspan=2&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.68%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=2% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 12.82%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none valign=bottom width=12% bgcolor=#CCEEFF colspan=2&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.04%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 2.25pt double; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 11.52%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=11% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;0.38&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.68%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=2% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 1.3%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 2.25pt double; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 11.52%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=11% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;0.15&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.04%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Subsequent Events&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 30pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Subsequent events are events or transactions that occur after the balance sheet date but before financial statements are issued.&amp;#160; We recognize in the financial statements the effects of all subsequent events that provide additional evidence about conditions that existed at the date of the balance sheet
 including the estimates inherent in the process of preparing the financial statements.&amp;#160; Our financial statements do not recognize subsequent events that provide evidence about conditions that did not exist at the date of the balance sheet but arose after the balance sheet date and before financial statements are issued.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 30pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Recent Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;In 2011
 the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&amp;#8220;FASB&amp;#8221;) issued two Accounting Standards Updates (&amp;#8220;ASUs&amp;#8221;)
 which amend the guidance for the presentation of comprehensive income.&amp;#160; The amended guidance eliminates the option to report other comprehensive income and its components in the statement of changes in equity.&amp;#160; Upon adoption
 other comprehensive income must be presented either in a single continuous statement of comprehensive income or in two separate but consecutive statements.&amp;#160; Although the new guidance changes the presentation of comprehensive income
 there are no changes to the components that are recognized in comprehensive income.&amp;#160; We adopted these ASUs in 2012 using two separate but consecutive statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;In July&amp;#160;2012
 the FASB issued new impairment testing requirements for indefinite-lived intangible assets.&amp;#160; Under the updated standard an entity would first perform a qualitative impairment test for indefinite-lived intangible assets to determine whether a quantitative assessment is necessary. The requirements are effective for annual and interim impairment tests for fiscal years beginning after September&amp;#160;15
 2012.&amp;#160; The Company adopted the requirements during fiscal year 2012
 but elected to continue to perform a quantitative impairment analysis for our indefinite-lived intangibles.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;2.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Goodwill

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;The trademarks are deemed to have an indefinite useful life because they are expected to generate cash flows indefinitely.&amp;#160; Amortization expense was $0.02 million and $0.04 million for the years ending December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively.&amp;#160; The non-compete agreements were fully amortized in May&amp;#160;2012.&amp;#160; As of December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 we expect amortization expense on these intangible assets over the next five years to be as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Goodwill and trademarks are reviewed for impairment annually in the fourth fiscal quarter
 or more frequently if impairment indicators arise.&amp;#160; Goodwill is required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change that more-likely-than-not reduces the fair value of a reporting unit below its carrying value.&amp;#160; Intangible assets with indefinite lives are required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change indicating that the asset might be impaired.&amp;#160; We believe the carrying values of our intangible assets are appropriate.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;3.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Accrued Liabilities:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Accrued liabilities consisted of the following as of December&amp;#160;29

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;The total cost of equipment and furniture and office equipment included in the table above held under capital lease obligations was $2.6 million and $3.7 million as of December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively.&amp;#160; Depreciation expense
 including amortization of property under capital leases
 for fiscal years 2012 and 2011 was $4.7 million and $4.6 million
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.62%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;To fund the acquisition of Rader Farms
 we entered into a Loan Agreement (the &amp;#8220;Loan Agreement&amp;#8221;) with U.S. Bank.&amp;#160; Each of our subsidiaries is a guarantor of the Loan Agreement
 which is secured by a pledge of all of the assets of our consolidated group.&amp;#160;&amp;#160; The borrowing capacity available to us under the Loan Agreement consists of notes representing:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol size=2&gt;&amp;#183;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;a revolving line of credit up to $25 million maturing on July&amp;#160;30
 2014;&amp;#160; At December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 $10.1 million was outstanding and
 based on eligible assets
 $10.3 million was available under the line of credit.&amp;#160; All borrowings under the revolving line of credit bear interest at either (i)&amp;#160;the prime rate of interest announced by U.S. Bank from time to time or (ii)&amp;#160;LIBOR
 plus the LIBOR Rate Margin (as defined in the revolving credit facility note as adjusted.)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol size=2&gt;&amp;#183;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Equipment term loan due May&amp;#160;2014.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol size=2&gt;&amp;#183;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Real estate term loan due July&amp;#160;2017.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 49.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13.5pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;As is customary in such financings
 U.S. Bank may terminate its commitments and accelerate the repayment of amounts outstanding and exercise other remedies upon the occurrence of an event of default (as defined in the Loan Agreement)
 subject
 in certain instances
 to the expiration of an applicable cure period.&amp;#160; The agreement requires us to maintain compliance with certain financial covenants
 including a minimum fixed charge coverage ratio and a leverage ratio.&amp;#160; At December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 we were in compliance with all of the financial covenants.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;In June&amp;#160;2012
 we paid off the remaining balance of $1.3 million on the maturing mortgage loan on the Goodyear facility using working capital.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 21.2%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=21% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;

&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 2.25pt; WIDTH: 4.68%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=4% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 21.2%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 2.25pt double valign=bottom width=21% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;(884
910&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 2.25pt; WIDTH: 1.82%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Interest Rate Swaps&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;To manage exposure to changing interest rates
 we selectively enter into interest rate swap agreements.&amp;#160; Our interest rate swaps qualify for and are designated as cash flow hedges.&amp;#160; Changes in the fair value of a swap that is highly effective and that is designated and qualifies as a cash flow hedge to the extent that the hedge is effective
 are recorded in other comprehensive income (loss).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We entered into an interest rate swap in 2006 to convert the interest rate of the mortgage to purchase the Bluffton
&amp;#160;Indiana plant from the contractual rate of 30 day LIBOR plus 165 basis points to a fixed rate of 6.85%.&amp;#160; The swap has a fixed pay-rate of 6.85% and a notional value of approximately $2.0 million and $2.1 million at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively
 and expires in December&amp;#160;2016.&amp;#160; We evaluate the effectiveness of the hedge on a quarterly basis and at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 the hedge is highly effective.&amp;#160; The interest rate swap had a fair value of $343
710 and $385
899 at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively
 which were recorded as a liability on the accompanying consolidated balance sheets.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The swap value was determined in accordance with the fair value measurement guidance discussed earlier using Level 2 observable inputs and approximates the loss that would have been realized if the contract had been settled at the end of the fiscal period.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We entered into another interest rate swap in January&amp;#160;2008 to effectively convert the interest rate on the real estate term loan to a fixed rate of 4.28%.&amp;#160; The interest rate swap is structured with decreasing notional values to match the expected pay down of the debt.&amp;#160; The notional value of the swap was $3.0 million and $3.2 million at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively.&amp;#160; The interest rate swap is accounted for as a cash flow hedge derivative and expires in July&amp;#160;2017.&amp;#160; We evaluate the effectiveness of the hedge on a quarterly basis and during the year ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 the hedge is highly effective. &amp;#160;The interest rate swap had fair value of $422
508 and $457
735 at December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 respectively
 which were recorded as a liability on the accompanying consolidated balance sheet.&amp;#160; This value was determined in accordance with the fair value measurement guidance discussed earlier using Level 2 observable inputs and approximates the loss that would have been realized if the contract had been settled at the end of the fiscal period.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;7.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Commitments and Contingencies:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We are periodically a party to various lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of business.&amp;#160; Management believes
 based on discussions with legal counsel
 that the resolution of such lawsuits
 individually and in the aggregate
 will not have a material adverse effect on our financial position or results of operations.&amp;#160; See Note 11
 &amp;#8220;Litigation&amp;#8221;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We lease one-half of a 200
000 square foot facility in Bluffton
&amp;#160;Indiana which is used as a distribution center.&amp;#160; This operating lease expires January&amp;#160;31
 2014 and current lease payments are approximately $32
500 per month.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We also lease approximately 13
865 square feet of office space in Phoenix
 Arizona
 which is used as our corporate headquarters.&amp;#160; The lease expires April&amp;#160;1
 2017 and current lease payments are approximately $26
000 per month.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We own a farming
 processing and storage facility located on 696 acres of land in Lynden
 Washington
 which is leased from the Uptrails Group LLC
 owned by three members of the Rader family.&amp;#160; One of the three
 Brad Rader
 is a current employee of ours and one of the others
 Sue Rader
 was a former owner of Rader Farms.&amp;#160; This operating lease commenced on the acquisition date and was extended in October&amp;#160;2012 through May&amp;#160;17
 2027.&amp;#160; Lease payments are $43
500 per month through May&amp;#160;17
 2017
 at which time they increase to $52
200 for the duration of the term of the lease.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;In addition to our facility and land leases
 we have entered into a variety of operating leases for equipment
 vehicles and office space.&amp;#160; Rental expense under all operating leases was $1.6 million and $1.7 million for fiscal 2012 and 2011
 respectively.&amp;#160; Minimum future rental commitments under non-cancelable leases as of December&amp;#160;29
 2012 are as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;td style=BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; WIDTH: 76.76%; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 1pt solid valign=bottom width=76%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=1&gt;Year&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

614
749&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.48%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We produce T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snacks
 Tato Skins&amp;#174; brand potato crisps and Boulder Canyon&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 6.5pt; POSITION: relative; TOP: -3pt size=1&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;&amp;#160;Natural Foods &amp;#160;Rice and Bean snacks utilizing a sheeting and frying process that includes technology that we license from a third party.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement between us and the third party
 we have a royalty-bearing
 exclusive right license to use the technology in the United States
 Canada
 and Mexico until such time the parties mutually agree to terminate the agreement.&amp;#160; Even though the patents for this technology expired in December 2006
 in consideration for the use of this technology
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of products manufactured utilizing the technology until such termination date.&amp;#160; However
 should products substantially similar to Tato Skins&amp;#174;
 O&amp;#8217;Boisies&amp;#174; and Pizzarias&amp;#174; become available for any reason in the marketplace by any manufacturer other than us which results in a sales decline of 10% or more
 any royalty obligation for the respective product(s)&amp;#160;shall cease.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We license the T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snacks trademark from T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring in May 2014.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of T.G.I. Friday&amp;#8217;s&amp;#174; brand snack products and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We license the Jamba&amp;#174; brand trademark from Jamba Juice Company under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2035.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Jamba&amp;#174; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We license the Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous&amp;#174; brand trademark from Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous Corporation under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2031.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Nathan&amp;#8217;s Famous&amp;#174; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We license the Vidalia&amp;#174; brand trademark from Vidalia Brands
&amp;#160;Inc. under a license agreement with a an initial term expiring January&amp;#160;2014
 which automatically extends for a five year period upon meeting certain minimum sales targets.&amp;#160; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Vidalia&amp;#174; brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;8.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 3pt size=1&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt size=2&gt;Shareholders&amp;#8217; Equity:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Restricted Stock Awards&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We have issued shares of restricted common stock as incentives to certain officers and members of the Board of Directors.&amp;#160; Restricted stock awards granted to officers contain performance restrictions which are required to be achieved over a three year measurement period in order for the shares to be awarded.&amp;#160; The number of performance-based restricted stock awards ultimately awarded varies based on whether we achieve certain financial results.&amp;#160; Restricted stock awards granted to members of the Board of Directors are granted with a one year service period.&amp;#160; We record compensation expense each period based on the market price of our common stock at the time of grant and our estimate of the most probable number of awards issued under grants of performance-based restricted stock awards.&amp;#160; The related stock-based compensation expense is included in selling
 general and administrative expenses.&amp;#160; Additionally
 the compensation expense is adjusted for our estimate of forfeitures.&amp;#160; Recipients of restricted common stock are entitled to receive any dividends declared on our common stock and have voting rights
 regardless of whether such shares have vested.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;During fiscal years 2011 and 2012
 restricted share activity was as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table style=MARGIN-LEFT: 0.7in; WIDTH: 80.66%; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=80% border=0&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;4.64&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BACKGROUND: #cceeff; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.28%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1% bgcolor=#CCEEFF&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;During the years ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011
 the total stock-based compensation expense from restricted stock recognized in the financial statements was $0.5 million and $0.6 million respectively.&amp;#160; There were no stock-based compensation costs which were capitalized.&amp;#160; As of December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 the total unrecognized costs related to non-vested restricted stock awards granted were $0.8 million and $0.9 million respectively.&amp;#160; We expect to recognize such costs in the financial statements over a weighted-average period of 0.85 years.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Preferred Stock&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;We have authorized 50
000 shares of $100 par value Preferred Stock
 none of which is outstanding.&amp;#160; We may issue such shares of Preferred Stock in the future without shareholder approval.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;Stock Options&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;The 2005 Plan was approved at our 2005 Annual Meeting of Shareholders and initially reserved for issuance&amp;#160;410
518 shares of Common Stock
 which is the number of reserved but unissued shares available for issuance under the 1995 Plan.&amp;#160; The number of shares of Common Stock reserved for issuance has been increased since 2005 to a total of 2
710
518 as of the date of this filing
 pursuant to a series of amendments to the 2005 Plan approved by our shareholders.&amp;#160; If any shares of Common Stock subject to awards granted under the 2005 Plan are canceled
 those shares will be available for future awards under the 2005 Plan.&amp;#160; The 2005 Plan expires in May&amp;#160;2015
 and awards granted under the 2005 Plan may include: nonqualified stock options
 incentive stock options
 restricted stock
 restricted stock units
 stock appreciation rights
 performance units and stock-reference awards.&amp;#160; Prior to May&amp;#160;2008
 all stock option grants had a five year term.&amp;#160; The fair value of these stock option grants is amortized to expense over the vesting period
 generally five years for employees and one year for the Board of Directors.&amp;#160; In May&amp;#160;2008
 our Board of Directors approved a 10 year term for all future stock option grants
 with vesting periods of five years and one year for employees and Board of Director members
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 39pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;As of December&amp;#160;29
 2012
 there were 430
292 shares of Common Stock available for Awards under the 2005 Plan
 plus 562
238 shares of Common Stock available for any Awards under the 2005 Plan other than Incentive Stock Options.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right align=right&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;6.5&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 1.26%; PADDING-TOP: 0in valign=bottom width=1%&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;The expected dividend yield was based on the fact that we have never issued a dividend and have no near term intent to do so.&amp;#160; The volatility assumption was based on historical volatility during the time period that corresponds to the expected life of the option.&amp;#160; The expected life (estimated period of time outstanding) of stock options granted was estimated based on historical exercise activity.&amp;#160; The risk-free interest rate assumption was based on the interest rate of U.S. Treasuries on the date the option was granted.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center align=center&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;During fiscal years 2012 and 2011
 stock option activity was as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;The total stock-based compensation expense from stock options recognized in the financial statements was $0.7 million and $0.4 million for the years ended December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 respectively
 which reduced income from operations accordingly.&amp;#160; There were no stock-based compensation costs which were capitalized.&amp;#160; As of December&amp;#160;29
 2012 and December&amp;#160;31
 2011 the total unrecognized costs related to non-vested stock options granted were $0.9 million and $0.7 million
 respectively.&amp;#160; We expect to recognize such costs in the financial statements over a weighted average period of 2.7 years.&amp;#160; This expected compensation expense does not reflect any new awards
 or modifications to existing awards
 that could occur in the future.&amp;#160; We issue new shares upon the exercise of stock options
 as opposed to reissuing treasury shares.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in&gt;&lt;font style=FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman size=2&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
